{"cursor":"1781","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"In heraldry, an 'augmentation' (often termed 'augmentation of honour' or\nsometimes 'augmentation of arms') is a modification or addition to a coat of\narms, typically given by a monarch as either a mere mark of favour, or a reward\nor recognition for some meritorious act. The grants of entire new coats by\nmonarchs as a reward are not augmentations, but rather grants of arms, and (in\ntheory) an augmentation mistakenly given to someone who did not have a right to\na coat would be nugatory.\n","linknr":116,"url":"Augmentation_(heraldry)","recorded":1364053248,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Augmentation_of_honour&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Augmentation_of_honour&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Augmentation_of_honour","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Augmentation_(heraldry)&redirect=no","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Heraldry","/wiki/Coat_of_arms","/wiki/Monarch","/wiki/Grant_of_arms","/w/index.php?title=Augmentation_of_honour&action=edit&section=1","/wiki/File:Thomas_Howard_Arms.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d6/Thomas_Howard_Arms.svg/109px-Thomas_Howard_Arms.svg.png","/wiki/Thomas_Howard,_2nd_Duke_of_Norfolk","/wiki/Ba